  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith spot at 6822 sitting just above the max negative gamma strike at 6820 (-40.6B), dealers are forced to buy this dip aggressively, creating strong support around current levels. The breakout regime with massive negative GEX (-89.6B total) means dealers will amplify any directional moves - buying strength toward 6840 resistance and selling weakness back through the 6820-6825 negative gamma cluster. Watch for violent reversals around 6820 and 6840 as dealers flip between buy/sell hedging, with the wall break and GEX surge events signaling we're in a high-volatility hedging zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect sharp bounces off 6820 support with potential rocket shots toward 6840 resistance.",
